# AetherForge
Local “ChatGPT-like” stack with internet access (browser tool), BudgetBase-style layout.

## Quick start (desktop)
1) Clone the repo on your PC (WSL recommended).
2) `cp .env.example .env` and adjust if needed.
3) `make bootstrap`
4) `make dev`

### What this repo contains
- `src/aetherforge/main.py`: minimal heartbeat that talks to your local LLM (Ollama or vLLM).
- `scripts/run_agent.sh`: convenience runner.
- `Makefile`: `bootstrap`, `dev`, `lint`, `test`.
- `.devcontainer/*`: optional—enables the same workflow in Dev Containers/Codespaces.

## Browse demo (desktop)
Start your local model (Ollama/vLLM), then:
```bash
make bootstrap
cp .env.example .env
chmod +x scripts/run_browse.sh
./scripts/run_browse.sh "Summarize <topic> and cite sources."
